FBCG: Normally the fund invests at least 80% of assets in blue chip companies (companies that, in Fidelity Management & Research Company LLC's (FMR) view, are well-known, well-established and well-capitalized), which generally have large or medium market capitalizations. It invests in companies that manager believes have above-average growth potential (stocks of these companies are often called "growth" stocks). The fund is non-diversified.
